### Server log

```text
[server] listening on 127.0.0.1:9443
[server] conn#1: GET / HTTP/1.1
[server] conn#1 (reused): GET / HTTP/1.1
```

This shows one TLS handshake and two HTTP requests over the same connection. Running T2 alone against the same server, with no pooled connection available, fails with `CURLE_PEER_FAILED_VERIFICATION`, confirming that the self-signed certificate is genuinely untrusted and that connection reuse is the mechanism.

